dialog.text:
It's a perfect fit for the pillows of the Wano Country indeed! Haha! Japanese culture is really fascinating, did you all know of the times when everyone had tied hair? Since everyone tied their hair on the upper side with topknots and whatnot, they had pillows like these. I remember my granny used one like this.

[[File:SBS99 Oden Concept.png|thumb|left|150px]]

Anyway, his original concept had a head like this. The top of his head was in the shape of a [[wikipedia:konjac|''konnyaku'']], an egg, and a ''ganmodoki'' (all ingredients that are usually put in skewers of Oden), but only the ''ganmodoki'' remained! In other words, it's called an ''Inokori-ganmodoki-doki-doki-doku-toku-mage'', or an “Overtime Ganmodoki Heart-throbbing Super-duper Uniquedo”.{{-}}
